title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: The sun is warm , the sky is clear ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: The waves are dancing fast and bright ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Blue isles and snowy mountains wear

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: The purple noon "s transparent might ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: The breath of the moist earth is light ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Around its unexpanded buds ;

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Like many a voice of one delight ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: The winds , the birds , the ocean floods ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: The City "s voice itself , is soft like Solitude "s .

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: I see the Deep "s untrampled floor

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: With green and purple seaweeds strown ;

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: I see the waves upon the shore ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Like light dissolved in star-showers , thrown :

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: I sit upon the sands alone ,—

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: The lightning of the noontide ocean

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Is flashing round me , and a tone

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Arises from its measured motion ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: How sweet ! did any heart now share in my emotion .

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Alas ! I have nor hope nor health ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Nor peace within nor calm around ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Nor that content surpassing wealth

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: The sage in meditation found ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: And walked with inward glory crowned —

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Nor fame , nor power , nor love , nor leisure .

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Others I see whom these surround —

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Smiling they live , and call life pleasure ;—

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: To me that cup has been dealt in another measure .

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Yet now despair itself is mild ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Even as the winds and waters are ;

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: I could lie down like a tired child ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: And weep away the life of care

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Which I have borne and yet must bear ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Till death like sleep might steal on me ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: And I might feel in the warm air

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: My cheek grow cold , and hear the sea

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Breathe o"er my dying brain its last monotony .

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Some might lament that I were cold ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: As I , when this sweet day is gone ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Which my lost heart , too soon grown old ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Insults with this untimely moan ;

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: They might lament — for I am one

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Whom men love not ,— and yet regret ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Unlike this day , which , when the sun

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Shall on its stainless glory set ,

title: STANZAS WRITTEN IN DEJECTION , NEAR NAPLES .
line_text: Will linger , though enjoyed , like joy in memory yet .

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: When my love swears that she is made of truth ,

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: I do believe her , though I know she lies ,

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: That she might think me some untutor "d youth ,

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: Unskilful in the world "s false forgeries ,

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: Outfacing faults in love with love "s ill rest .

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: And wherefore say not I that I am old ?

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: O , love "s best habit is a soothing tongue ,

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: And age , in love , loves not to have years told .

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: Therefore , I "ll lie with love , and love with me ,

title: The Passionate Pilgrim I .
line_text: Since that our faults in love thus smother "d be .

title: My Love Is Like To Ice

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: In vain , in vain — the all-composing Hour

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Resistless falls : the Muse obeys the Pow"r .

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: She comes ! she comes ! the sable Throne behold

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Of Night primæval and of Chaos old !

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Before her , Fancy "s gilded clouds decay ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: And all its varying Rain-bows die away .

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Wit shoots in vain its momentary fires ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: The meteor drops , and in a flash expires .

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: As one by one , at dread Medea "s strain ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: The sick"ning stars fade off th ’ ethereal plain ;

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: As Argus ’ eyes by Hermes ’ wand opprest ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Clos "d one by one to everlasting rest ;

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Thus at her felt approach , and secret might ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Art after Art goes out , and all is Night .

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: See skulking Truth to her old cavern fled ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Mountains of Casuistry heap "d o"er her head !

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Philosophy , that lean "d on Heav"n before ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Shrinks to her second cause , and is no more .

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Physic of Metaphysic begs defence ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: And Metaphysic calls for aid on Sense !

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: See Mystery to Mathematics fly !

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: In vain ! they gaze , turn giddy , rave , and die .

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Religion blushing veils her sacred fires ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: And unawares Morality expires .

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: For public Flame , nor private , dares to shine ;

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Nor human Spark is left , nor Glimpse divine !

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Lo ! thy dread Empire , CHAOS ! is restor "d ;

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Light dies before thy uncreating word ;

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: Thy hand , great Anarch ! lets the curtain fall ,

title: THE DESCENT OF DULLNESS
line_text: And universal Darkness buries All .

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: I met a traveller from an antique land

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: Who said : Two vast and trunkless legs of stone

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: Stand in the desert ... Near them , on the sand ,

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: Half sunk , a shattered visage lies , whose frown ,

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: And wrinkled lip , and sneer of cold command ,

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: Tell that its sculptor well those passions read

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: Which yet survive , stamped on these lifeless things ,

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: The hand that mocked them , and the heart that fed :

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: And on the pedestal these words appear :

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: ‘ My name is Ozymandias , king of kings :

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: Look on my works , ye Mighty , and despair ! ’

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: Nothing beside remains . Round the decay

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: Of that colossal wreck , boundless and bare

title: OZYMANDIAS
line_text: The lone and level sands stretch far away .

title: Desert Places
line_text: Snow falling and night falling fast, oh, fast

title: Desert Places
line_text: In a field I looked into going past,

title: Desert Places
line_text: And the ground almost covered smooth in snow,

title: Desert Places
line_text: But a few weeds and stubble showing last.

title: Desert Places
line_text: The woods around it have it--it is theirs.

title: Desert Places
line_text: All animals are smothered in their lairs.

title: Desert Places
line_text: I am too absent-spirited to count;

title: Desert Places
line_text: The loneliness includes me unawares.

title: Desert Places
line_text: And lonely as it is that loneliness

title: Desert Places
line_text: Will be more lonely ere it will be less--

title: Desert Places
line_text: A blanker whiteness of benighted snow

title: Desert Places
line_text: With no expression, nothing to express.

title: Desert Places
line_text: They cannot scare me with their empty spaces

title: Desert Places
line_text: Between stars--on stars where no human race is.

title: Desert Places
line_text: I have it in me so much nearer home

title: Desert Places
line_text: To scare myself with my own desert places.

title: If—
line_text: If you can keep your head when all about you

title: If—
line_text: Are losing theirs and blaming it on you,

title: If—
line_text: If you can trust yourself when all men doubt you,

title: If—
line_text: But make allowance for their doubting too;

title: If—
line_text: If you can wait and not be tired by waiting,

title: If—
line_text: Or being lied about, don’t deal in lies,

title: If—
line_text: Or being hated, don’t give way to hating,

title: If—
line_text: And yet don’t look too good, nor talk too wise:

title: If—
line_text: If you can dream—and not make dreams your master;

title: If—
line_text: If you can think—and not make thoughts your aim;

title: If—
line_text: If you can meet with Triumph and Disaster

title: If—
line_text: And treat those two impostors just the same;

title: If—
line_text: If you can bear to hear the truth you’ve spoken

title: If—
line_text: Twisted by knaves to make a trap for fools,

title: If—
line_text: Or watch the things you gave your life to, broken,

title: If—
line_text: And stoop and build ’em up with worn-out tools:

title: If—
line_text: If you can make one heap of all your winnings

title: If—
line_text: And risk it on one turn of pitch-and-toss,

title: If—
line_text: And lose, and start again at your beginnings

title: If—
line_text: And never breathe a word about your loss;

title: If—
line_text: If you can force your heart and nerve and sinew

title: If—
line_text: To serve your turn long after they are gone,

title: If—
line_text: And so hold on when there is nothing in you

title: If—
line_text: Except the Will which says to them: ‘Hold on!’

title: If—
line_text: If you can talk with crowds and keep your virtue,

title: If—
line_text: Or walk with Kings—nor lose the common touch,

title: If—
line_text: If neither foes nor loving friends can hurt you,

title: If—
line_text: If all men count with you, but none too much;

title: If—
line_text: If you can fill the unforgiving minute

title: If—
line_text: With sixty seconds’ worth of distance run,

title: If—
line_text: Yours is the Earth and everything that’s in it,

title: If—
line_text: And—which is more—you’ll be a Man, my son!

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: A noiseless patient spider ,

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: I mark "d where on a little promontory it stood isolated ,

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: Mark "d how to explore the vacant vast surrounding ,

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: It launch "d forth filament , filament , filament out of itself ,

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: Ever unreeling them , ever tirelessly speeding them .

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: And you O my soul where you stand ,

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: Surrounded , detached , in measureless oceans of space ,

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: Ceaselessly musing , venturing , throwing , seeking the spheres to

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: connect them ,

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: Till the bridge you will need be form "d , till the ductile anchor hold ,

title: A Noiseless Patient Spider
line_text: Till the gossamer thread you fling catch somewhere , O my soul .

title: LONDON
line_text: In every cry of every man ,

title: LONDON
line_text: In every infant "s cry of fear ,

title: LONDON
line_text: In every voice , in every ban ,

title: LONDON
line_text: The mind-forged manacles I hear :

title: LONDON
line_text: How the chimney-sweeper "s cry

title: LONDON
line_text: Every blackening church appalls ,

title: LONDON

line_text: Blasts the new-born infant "s tear ,

title: LONDON
line_text: And blights with plagues the marriage-hearse .

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: I wandered lonely as a Cloud

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: That floats on high over Vales and Hills ,

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: When all at once I saw a crowd

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: A host of dancing Daffodills ;

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: Along the Lake , beneath the trees ,

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: Ten thousand dancing in the breeze .

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: Continuous as the stars that shine

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: And twinkle on the milky way,

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: They stretched in never-ending line

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: Along the margin of a bay:

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: Ten thousand saw I at a glance,

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: Tossing their heads in sprightly dance.

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: The waves beside them danced , but they

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: Outdid the sparkling waves in glee :—

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: A Poet could not but be gay

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: In such a laughing company :

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: I gazed — and gazed — but little thought

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: What wealth the shew to me had brought :

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: For oft when on my couch I lie

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: In vacant or in pensive mood ,

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: They flash upon that inward eye

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: Which is the bliss of solitude ,

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: And then my heart with pleasure fills ,

title: I wandered lonely as a Cloud
line_text: And dances with the Daffodils .
